ngfund.org/images/you_tube_logo.png\" style=\"border-width: 0px; border-style: solid; float: left; width: 85px; height: 31px; margin-right: 10px; \" /></a></strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong><a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/settlementhousing\" target=\"_blank\">www.youtube.com/settlementhousing</a></strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong><span style=\"color: white\">&nbsp;</span></strong></p>','2009-09-26','yes'),(22,23,'easy_green','Annual Benefit','<hr />\r\n<h3>\r\n	<span style=\"color: rgb(105, 105, 105);\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">2010 Easy to be Green</span></span></span></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style=\"color: rgb(105, 105, 105);\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">A great and green time was had by all at Settlement Housing Fund&#39;s annual benefit at Landmark on the Park on May 25th.&nbsp; The event honored three great champions of affordable housing: Lieutenant Governor Richard Ravitch, past CEO and President of the National Housing Conference, Conrad Egan, and Capital One Bank, represented by Manhattan Market President, James Covington.&nbsp; Settlement Housing Fund has enjoyed long relationships with its honorees and was pleased to bring them together for this special evening attended by over 300 people from the affordable housing and real estate development communities.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style=\"color: rgb(105, 105, 105);\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">Settlement Housing Fund is pleased to thank everyone who&nbsp;supported the event, which benefits our work to create and sustain affordable housing and community programs throughout the city. &nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3>\r\n	<span style=\"color: rgb(105, 105, 105);\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">2009 Shovel Ready and Raring to Go</span></span></span></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style=\"color: rgb(105, 105, 105);\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">Over 300 people attended Settlement Housing Fund&#39;s 20th Annual benefit at Landmark on the Park on June 4th.&nbsp;The event honored Nick Lembo, President of Monadnock Construction, and the Fund for the City of New York.&nbsp; With hard hats and scaffolding on hand, we celebrated both these two great friends of Settlement Housing Fund and our &quot;shovel ready&quot; project, the New Settlement Community Campus.&nbsp; Nick Lembo, a leading builder of affordable housing, was our partner on a complex of 37 two-family homes in Brooklyn that we sold, predominantly to families who lived in public housing.&nbsp; And the Fund for the City of New York gave us our first grant to start our organization in 1969 and has been there for us since with its cash-flow loan program, which helps nonprofit groups manage their short-term needs while waiting for government reimbursements.&nbsp; Mary McCormick, the Fund&#39;s President, and Andrew Walrond, Loan Officer, accepted the award. We are grateful to our honorees, our Committee, and the many friends and colleagues who supported the event.</span></span></span></p>','2009-09-26','yes'),(23,24,'gbreak','Groundbreakings','<h3>\r\n	<span style=\"color: rgb(105,105,105)\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif\">New Settlement Community Campus&nbsp;Groundbreaking</span></span></h3>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify\">\r\n	<span style=\"color: rgb(105,105,105)\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px\"><span>On August 11, 2009, Settlement Housing Fund and New Settlement Apartments hosted a groundbreaking for the New Settlement Community Campus on Jerome Avenue in the Mount Eden neighborhood of the Bronx.<span>&nbsp; </span>Community members were joined by friends and supporters at the construction site of the future Campus, a pre-K through 12th grade public school and private nonprofit community center with swimming pool, art and dance studios, amphitheater and green roof terrace.&nbsp; The Campus will offer a unique model, as the school and community center facilities will be shared by the students and members of the community.&nbsp;&nbsp; This 172,000&nbsp;sq. ft.&nbsp;Campus will cost $83.3 million and Settlement Housing Fund&nbsp;must raise nearly $16 million for the community center and pool.&nbsp; Construction will be complete so the school can open in 2012.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\">\r\n	<span style=\"color: rgb(105,105,105)\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px\"><span>Speaking at the event were: Richard Ravitch, New York State Lieutenant Governor;<span>&nbsp; </span>Dennis Walcott, New York City Deputy Mayor for Education and Community Development; Aurelia Greene, Bronx Deputy Borough President; Maria Baez, Bronx Coucilmember; Vanessa Gibson, New York State Assemblywoman; Sharon Greenberger, President and CEO, NYC School Construction Authority; Dominic Carter, NY1 News Host/Senior Political Reporter; Jack Doyle, New Settlement Apartments Executive Director; and Carol Lamberg, Settlement Housing Fund Executive Director.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp; It </span>was hailed as a great day for the Bronx, where this facility will bring further revitalization and significant education, recreation and arts resources to the community.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\">\r\n	<span style=\"font-size: 16px\"><b><u>More Information</u></b><br />\r\n	&bull; <a href=\"http://www.settlementhousingfund.org/press.html\">Media Links</a><br />\r\n	&bull; <a href=\"http://www.settlementhousingfund.org/pdf/shfbroNOV3b.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">New Settlement Community Campus Brochure</a><br />\r\n	</span></p>','2009-09-26','yes'),(24,25,'upcoming','Upcoming Events','<h2 style=\"color: rgb(9, 107, 172);\">\r\n	Thanks to all who supported our annual benefit.</h2>\r\n<h2 style=\"color: rgb(9, 107, 172);\">\r\n	<span style=\"color: rgb(246, 159, 79); font-size: 12px;\"><em>Photo: Secretary Shaun Donovan, Alexa Sewell, President, Settlement Housing Fund, Charles Warren, Chairman, Settlement Housing Fund, Joan Tally, Morgan Stanley Global Finance, Mathew Wambua, RHR Funding, A Richman Group Company at Standing Up for Strong Neighborhoods, June 12th, Tribeca Rooftop.</em></span></h2>\r\n<h2 style=\"color: rgb(9, 107, 172);\">\r\n	Upcoming Event: Wednesday, July 23th, 6 pm</h2>\r\n<h2 style=\"color: rgb(9, 107, 172);\">\r\n	<span style=\"color: rgb(246, 159, 79); font-size: 12px;\"><em>Opening reception for our new Hearts of Gold Children&#39;s Tutoring Program at Semiperm, Settlement Housing Fund&#39;s residence for formerly homeless single parent famlies on W. 102nd Street. &nbsp;For details, contact Nicole at nclare@shfinc.org.</em></span></h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>','2009-09-26','yes'),(28,36,'p_overview','Program Overview','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt\">\r\n	<span style=\"color: rgb(105,105,105)\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px\">We plan, we develop, we build, we market, we supervise management and maintenance, but that is not all.<span>&nbsp; </span>When the resources are there, we work with residents and neighborhood organizations to develop community programs and commercial establishments.<span>&nbsp; </span>We have created educational programs, youth programs, teen recreation, safety, and health care amenities, and whatever it takes to make neighborhoods viable and to provide opportunities for upward mobility.<span>&nbsp; </span>We also work as development and marketing consultants for both non-profit and for-profit owners.<span>&nbsp; </span></span></span></p>','2009-10-08','yes'),(30,41,'priv1','Privacy Policy','<p>\r\n<!--StartFragment--></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;margin-bottom:11.25pt;\r\nline-height:125%;mso-outline-level:2\">\r\n<!--StartFragment--></p>\r\n<p