	<span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Arial, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\">Lance H. Wilson, Oppenheimer Multifamily Housing &amp; Healthcare Finance, Inc.</span></span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style=\"font-size:14px;\">Related Management</span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style=\"font-size:14px;\">Carmi Bee and Peter Bafitis, RKTB Architects, P.C.</span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Arial, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\">Niall Murray, Rockabill Advisors</span></span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style=\"font-size:14px;\">Alan Zaretsky, Rotavele Elevator Inc.</span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style=\"font-size:14px;\">Laura and Brad Sacks&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style=\"font-size:14px;\">Marlene and Edward Shufro</span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style=\"font-size:14px;\">James Knepper, SKA Marin</span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style=\"font-size:14px;\">Stephen and Jane Kurr Sussman</span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Arial, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">TF Cornerstone Inc.</span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style=\"font-size:14px;\">Trinity Place Holdings, Inc.</span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style=\"font-size:14px;\">Michael Schmelzer, Tryax Realty Management, Inc.</span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Raymond H. Yu, Yuco Real Estate Company, Inc.</span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h4>\r\n	<span style=\"color:#808080;\"><span style=\"font-family:arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\">2013 In The Clouds Celebration</span></span></span></h4>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"color:#808080;\">Nearly 300 friends and supporters joined us for a special night at the Chelsea Piers Sunset Terrace to honor visionary leaders and community builders. &nbsp;Glass brick awards went to&nbsp;Bronx Borough President Ruben Diaz Jr.&nbsp;and&nbsp;City Council Member Helen Diane Foster&nbsp;for their instrumental role in helping us create the&nbsp;</span><a href=\"http://pinterest.com/shfinc/new-settlement-community-campus/\"><span style=\"color:#808080;\">New Settlement Community Center</span></a><span style=\"color:#808080;\">.&nbsp;&nbsp;And&nbsp;Carol Lamberg&nbsp;was recognized for her thirty years of work as Settlement Housing Fund&#39;s Executive Director, which has included the creation of nearly 9,000 units of quality affordable housing as well as amenities and programs throughout New York City</span>.</span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><a href=\"http://web.sendtoprint.net/proofbook/galleries.asp?CouponID=Badini&amp;skip=15\"><u><strong>PHOTOS</strong></u></a></span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a href=\"http://www.settlementhousingfund.org/images/top/building_holder6.jpg\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.settlementhousingfund.org/images/top/in_the_cloud.jpg\" style=\"width: 540px; height: 360px; float: left; border-width: 0px; border-style: solid;\" /></a></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style=\"color:#808080;\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">Charles S. Warren, Board President and Event Chair</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style=\"color:#808080;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">Gary Jacob and Jeffrey E. Levine, Event Vice Chairs&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(128, 128, 128);\">Many thanks to all of our event sponsors, contributors and members of the Cumulus Celebration Committee.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h4>\r\n	<span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(105, 105, 105);\">2012 Juggling for Strong and Healthy Communities</span></span></h4>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style=\"font-family:arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color:#808080;\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\">We had a ball on June 5th at Landmark on the Park celebrating our collective juggling for community development. &nbsp;We were proud to honor HPD Commissioner Mathew Wambua and FG-PH Corp., an excellent affordable housing contractor. &nbsp;The glass brick award was presented to Commissioner Wambua by&nbsp;Special Guest Presenter Robert K. Steel, Deputy Mayor for Economic Development. &nbsp;Event Chair Chuck Brass presented the award to FG-PH. &nbsp;We also enjoyed brief remarks by Settlement Housing Fund&nbsp;Board President Charles S. Warren and Executive Director Carol Lamberg, and were thoroughly entertained by jugglers Jen Slaw and Michael Karas.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><a href=\"http://www.facebook.com/media/set/?set=a.457335607664501.110671.242527502478647&amp;type=1\"><u><strong>PHOTOS</strong></u></a></span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style=\"color:#808080;\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\">We thank all our supporters and offer special thanks to our event sponsors and friends committee.</span></span></p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h4>\r\n	<span style=\"font-size: 14px\"><span style=\"color: rgb(105,105,105)\">2011 Cole with Soul and a Melody for CPC</span></span></h4>\r\n<div>\r\n	<span style=\"font-size: 14px\"><span style=\"color: #696969\">Many thanks to all who supported our annual benefit on June 1st at Landmark on the Park in honor of Susan Cole and&nbsp;The Community Preservation Corporation. Susan Cole retired from&nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"color: rgb(105,105,105); font-size: 14px\">Settlement Housing Fund&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size: 14px\"><span style=\"color: #696969\">in 2010 after 37 tireless years.&nbsp; In addition to her leadership role as Associate Director, she was the&nbsp;marketing guru, asset manager and overall fountain of wisdom and humor for the Board, staff and colleagues. &nbsp;Susan&#39;s love of soul music, and pride for the musicians at Settlement Housing Fund, inspired the event&#39;s theme and entertainment. &nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"color: rgb(105,105,105); font-size: 14px\">Our second honoree, Community Preservation Corporation, has financed the creation and preservation of hundreds of thousands of apartments. Settlement Housing Fund&#39;s founder, the late Clara Fox, was an ardent&nbsp;fan of CPC from its earliest days and a mentor to its former President, Michael Lappin. We give&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color: rgb(105,105,105); font-size: 14px\">special thanks to the Settlement H</span><span style=\"color: rgb(105,105,105); font-size: 14px\">ousing Fund Soul Singers, whose awesome performance brought our event to life, and to our event Co-Chairs&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color: rgb(105,105,105); font-size: 14px\">Robert Berne and Barbara J. Fife.&nbsp;</span></div>','2011-03-21','yes');
